Running Proxmox on TerraMaster F8 SSD Plus with multiple NVMEs and VT-D enabled
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Go to F8 SSD Plus system Bios and disable VT-D, save Bios and reboot/boot system,

2. Modify /etc/default/grub file to include/update GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT to have:
- pci=nommconf
- pcie_acs_override=downstream, intel_iommu=on, iommu=pt

Here is how GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT should look after modification:
GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="pci=nommconf pcie_acs_override=downstream intel_iommu=on iommu=pt"

Notes:
- pci=nommconf -> necessary to be able to boot with VT-D enabled
- pcie_acs_override=downstream, intel_iommu=on, iommu=pt -> for IOMMU and IOMMU isolation to work

3. Save /etc/default/grub

4. Run update-grub command

5. Reboot F8 SSD Plus system

6. In Bios, re-enable VT-D, save and start F8 SSD Plus system

Now you should have F8 SSD Plus system with mutiple NVMEs and Proxmox working with VT-D enabled.
